1 (VI) A TECHNICIAN.
2 (3) A CLINICAL STAFFING COMMITTEE ESTABLISHED UNDER
3 PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION MAY INCLUDE A PATIENT ADVOCATE.
4 (D) EACH CLINICAL STAFFING COMMITTEE SHALL DEVELOP A CLINICAL
5 STAFFING PLAN FOR THE HOSPITAL THAT ESTABLISHES THE APPROPRIATE NUMBER
6 OF CLINICIANS NEEDED TO ADMINISTER QUALITY HEALTH CARE BY SETTING.
7 (E) (1) WHEN DEVELOPING A CLINICAL STAFFING PLAN, THE CLINICAL
8 STAFFING COMMITTEE SHALL ESTABLISH, BASED ON THE PATIENT POPULATION OF
9 THE HOSPITAL:
10 (I) SUGGESTED GUIDELINES OR RATIOS, MATRICES, OR GRIDS
11 INDICATING HOW MANY PATIENTS SHOULD BE ASSIGNED TO EACH REGISTERED
12 NURSE BY UNIT OR SETTING; AND
13 (II) THE NUMBER OF REGISTERED NURSES, LICENSED
14 PRACTICAL NURSES, CERTIFIED NURSING ASSISTANTS, CERTIFIED MEDICINE
15 TECHNICIANS, ENVIRONMENTAL SERVICE WORKERS, AND ANCILLARY MEMBERS OF
16 THE DIRECT CARE TEAM THAT SHOULD BE PRESENT ON EACH UNIT DURING EACH
17 SHIFT.
18 (2) TO THE EXTENT PRACTICABLE, THE GUIDELINES ESTABLISHED
19 UNDER PARAGRAPH (1)(I) OF THIS SUBSECTION SHALL BE BASED ON NATIONAL
20 EVIDENCE–BASED STANDARDS.
21 (F) ON OR BEFORE JULY 1 EACH YEAR, EACH HOSPITAL, THROUGH THE
22 CLINICAL STAFFING COMMITTEE, SHALL CONDUCT A REVIEW OF THE CLINICAL
23 STAFFING PLAN TO:
24 (1) EVALUATE THE EFFECTIVENESS OF THE CLINICAL STAFFING
25 PLAN DURING THE IMMEDIATELY PRECEDING YEAR;
26 (2) UPDATE THE CLINICAL STAFFING PLAN TO ENSURE THAT THE
27 CLINICAL STAFFING PLAN CONTINUES TO BE APPROPRIATE AND EFFECTIVE; AND
28 (3) DEVELOP A PROCESS FOR RECEIVING, RESOLVING, AND
29 TRACKING COMPLAINTS RELATED TO THE CLINICAL STAFFING PLAN.
30 (G) IN DEVELOPING THE CLINICAL STAFFING PLAN, THE CLINICAL
31 STAFFING COMMITTEE SHALL CONSIDER:

